<!DOCTYPE html> <html> <body> <p>The build stage of the CI/CD pipeline deals with building each individual microservice to see whether they compile or not.</p><p><img src="https://portfolio.drieam.app/api/public/v1/blobs/545ea1b8-b9c6-4fdf-9e1d-cab50ed05fbf/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBeit6QXc9PSIsImV4cCI6bnVsbCwicHVyIjoiYmxvYl9pZCJ9fQ==--216b00d81a41372823fb9d72737ac3136b8dc59e/image_2024-05-25_221937611.png" data-key="vkzhzv3nffafrj2c9mj67q7egz50"></p><p>This is done in order to determine whether there is an immediate fault with compiling the code to javascript, since running the microservices locally the code is interpreted directly from typescript and some errors in the code can still result to a successful launch in dev mode.</p><p>The code for building the authentication microservice in the gitlab CI definition file is as follows:</p><pre><code># Build build-auth-ms: extends: .build_template script: - !reference [.common_scripts, npm_auth_ms] - npm run build</code></pre><p>The code for the other microservices is identical. It executes a few common scripts defined on a top level in the gitlab-ci.yml file, in order to avoid repetition, such as installing npm packages. Afterwards it run the build command.</p> </body> </html>